                        "id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "value": "understanding-anxiety"
                        },
                        "thumbnail": {
                            "type": "image",
                            "value": {
                                "src": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "value": "assets/portrait-happy-asian-woman-smiling-posing-confident-cross-arms-chest-standing-against-studio-background-sqim5icd.jpg"
                                },
                                "alt": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "value": "Person smiling with confidence"
                                }
                            }
                        },
                        "title": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "value": "Understanding Anxiety: When Worry Becomes More Than Everyday Stress"
                        },
                        "publishedDate": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "value": "March 12, 2026"
                        },
                        "body": {
                            "type": "richtext",
                            "value": "Anxiety is one of the most common mental health concerns we see in practice. While occasional worry is a normal part of life, persistent anxiety can affect sleep, concentration, relationships, and daily functioning.\n\nAt Elevate Mental Health and Wellness, we take a whole-person approach. That means looking at your symptoms in context: your history, your environment, and your goals for care. Treatment may include psychotherapy, medication management, lifestyle adjustments, or a combination tailored to you.\n\nIf anxiety is interfering with your life, you do not have to manage it alone. Reaching out is the first step toward feeling more grounded and in control."
                        },
